article.headline: LIU Brooklyn 75, Wagner 60
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Williams scored 17 points to lead Long Island to a 75-60 win over Wagner on Friday night. Eugene Kotorobai added 11 points for the visiting Blackbirds (11-15, 8-9 Northeast Conference), who led 41-30 at halftime. Williams went 5-for-10 from 3-point range and Long Island finished 15-of-30 from behind the arc. Durell Vinson had 16 points and 12 rebounds and DeEarnest McLemore scored 14 points for the Seahawks (12-14, 5-12). Vinson made a jumper to tie it at 11 with 13:57 left in the first half. Long Island then put together a 14-0 run to take control. Kotorobai made two of the Blackbirds' four 3-pointers during the surge. Long Island connected on 11 of 20 3-pointers in the first half. Matt Vitale made a 3 to pull Wagner within 41-33 early in the second half but the Blackbirds responded with a 13-4 spurt. Williams' layup made it 54-37 with 15:47 remaining.
